Commissioner Bud Selig and Major League Baseball have taken a lot of heat over the last several months for their supposed failure to grapple forthrightly with the sport's steroid problem. Before the mid-1990s, the substances of choice in the clubhouse were amphetamines and recreational drugs. At the time, many anabolic steroids were illegal if purchased without a prescription. Indeed, it was probably around 10 years ago that some people in baseball became aware that anabolic steroids were being used by some players. 